JOY for ROS kinetic
Drivers for a generic Linux joystick.
Package contains joy_node, a node that interfaces a generic Linux joystick to ROS.
The node is publishing a sensor_msgs/Joy message, which contains the current state of each one of the joystick's button and axes.

official documentation:
* http://docs.ros.org/api/joy/html/

download:
* https://github.com/ros-drivers/joystick_drivers/tree/master/joy

installation:
* create ros package in src directory in ~/caktin_ws
* clone GitHub repo above in newly created package
* catkin_make package

getting started:
* connect wireless joysticks dongle to a computer
* start joy joy_node with rosrun command
* wait until the joystick is ready
* every button-press will be logged into joy topic
